<br>
Hello!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I too am from another server or two with 50 +s on both and I too quickly grow weary of staging for 6 hours to fight for 32 seconds. Many wonderous things could be done with one single group ( two groups as well ) without getting the feelings of being *just another face in the crowd* which if you feel that way it's a shame.<br>
<br>
I love the game that's EQ but I've come to FV in hopes of finding a very VERY tight knit group of people to play with. One to two groups. That many people can have alot of fun and great memories together as well as while working their way up outfit themselves to the point they need to be to be effective. Pre 50 Class Specific, drop and player made armor, post 50 Thurgandin quest armor can be done with one group <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Sebilis , Howling stones ect can be crawled with one and two groups very effectively for nice armor and weapons. It's all out there without using 40-60 people to Kill Trak.. And Naggy, and Cazic... And...and... <br>
<br>
So basically what I'm asking is you people that want to get to 60 without the hogwash that is a big guild (no offence to big guilds <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   it just isn't me anymore ) Where are you? What do you play? And would you like to hook up, get to know eash other and form a very small but very skilled group of like minded individuals and om gosh even friends heheh to play away your free time and have fun? I just started on FV a few weeks back and I've just been looking about trying to deciede what I'm going to be (currently a lvl 6 Iksar SK named Cyths) but if a few people stepped forward and said (we are humans, Good Alignment and we need a Wizard. I would be swayed that direction. I'm just looking for companions because that my friends is what makes the game. <br>
<br>
The end game is ok....<br>
<br>
Getting there is half the fun!!!<br>
<br>
Who you get there with is most important.<br>
<br>
<br>
/salute<br>
<br>
