Nice post.<br>
<br>
Though I am already 35 and trying to grind through that hellish level I am in the same boat as you.  As I have put in many posts your past is my past in sorts and the plan you have for FV is exactly what I have been doing for the last month.  I play almost 99% with my wife who is an Ogre Shaman 35 and I am and Ogre SK 35.  If you move through the levels and reach a point where you are of reasonable level to group feel free to send me a hello.  In 10 levels or so I forsee Scratchy and I to be doing about 50-60% groups and having a group of people who play at similar times always helps.  We dont plan to play for 10 hours at a time etc but dungeon crawls for 3-4 hours are nice.  Grouping up to help someone take down a mob for a specific item is nice.<br>
<br>
Though we havent grouped a lot we have buffed the heck out of a lot of people, saved a few, RP'd a ton and I have killed a small list of Gfay's finest Muhahahhahahaha.....I just love Elf steak <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Scratchy just took down an elf last night in which in all rights was rather 1 sided event.  I was very impressed with her Shaman skills.(I didnt know Shamen were so damn tough...geesh)  We had a nice dinner of elf steak last night.<br>
<br>
Anyhow well met and look forward to seeing your scaley self in FV.<br>
<br>
Ichi<br>
